gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Bucks 113, Clippers 106
gameRecap.excerpt: Milwaukee closes the game out on a 23-10 run to defeat Los Angeles, 113-106. For Milwaukee, Damian Lillard led the way with 41 points and four assists while Bobby Portis added 28 points and 16 rebounds in the victory. Paul George recorded 29 points, five rebounds, and two steals with James Harden tallying 29 points and eight assists for Los Angeles in the losing effort. Milwaukee improves to 41-21 on the season, while Los Angeles moves to 39-21 with the loss.
